---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import BiocareValues from '../components/BiocareValues.astro';
import PageHero from '../components/PageHero.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="About Us" description="St. John Biocare is a SEC-registered foundation born from one family's experience of kidney failure — our story, mission, values and leadership." image="/images/og/og-about.jpg">
  <PageHero
    image="/images/heroes/about-hero.webp"
    alt="An adult son resting a reassuring hand on his elderly father's shoulder, both smiling"
    eyebrow="Our story"
    title="A foundation, born from a real family story."
    subtitle="Not a corporate chain, but a foundation — born from one son's love for his mother, and a refusal to let excellent dialysis be a privilege of the few."
  />

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:760px" class:list={['stack']}>
      <p>
        It began in a family, in a hard season. A son watched his mother face end-stage renal
        disease and walked every step of it beside her — the hospital, the fear, the slow new
        rhythm of dialysis that would now shape her weeks. And in the middle of it, he saw
        something he would never forget: just how much truly <em>excellent</em> care can change,
        not only for the patient in the chair, but for the whole family holding its breath around
        her.
      </p>
      <p>
        He also saw how rare that care could be — and he refused to accept it. When his mother
        moved to outpatient dialysis, what the family found at existing centers convinced him of
        one thing: someone had to do this better. So, with a lifelong friend and partner, he
        decided that someone would be them. The idea grew from something simple and stubborn —
        compassion, and an unwavering grit for excellence.
      </p>
      <p>
        One conviction drove them, and still does: world-class hemodialysis should never be a
        privilege of the few. It should reach the many — ordinary Filipino families — without ever
        asking them to trade their safety for what they can afford. Not someday. Here, and now.
      </p>
      <p>
        On <strong>June 28, 2011</strong>, that resolve became real: St. John Biocare was
        registered with the SEC, and its first clinic opened in Quezon City on
        <strong>October 16, 2011</strong>. We were built as a non-stock <strong>foundation</strong>
        on purpose — it means we answer to a mission, not to shareholders. What started as one
        family's promise is now a growing network of centers, and we are only getting started.
      </p>

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>Our care philosophy</strong>
        <p style="margin:.4rem 0 0">
          “The St. John Biocare Way is to put the patient first… we must see the world through
          the eyes of our patients and their families.” We call the people we serve
          <strong>client-patients</strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--sand">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:820px">
      <div class="grid grid--2">
        <div class="card">
          <h2 style="font-size:1.35rem">Our vision</h2>
          <p><em>“To become the leading free-standing dialysis center and diagnostic facility
          in providing exemplary service to patients with end-stage renal disease.”</em></p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <h2 style="font-size:1.35rem">Our mission</h2>
          <p><em>“To provide the best-quality expert clinical care through state-of-the-art,
          innovative and affordable hemodialysis treatments and diagnostics manned by
          outstanding and compassionate personnel, responsive to the needs of our patients.”</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="center" style="margin-bottom:30px">
        <p class="eyebrow">What we stand for</p>
        <h2>The BIOCARE values.</h2>
      </div>
      <BiocareValues />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
